00:10:43.309 --> 00:10:46.354
if the client did not consent
to the sadistic act,

00:10:46.437 --> 00:10:48.273
it could constitute assault.

00:10:48.356 --> 00:10:49.274
That's right.

00:10:49.357 --> 00:10:50.900
I actually asked her that.

00:10:50.984 --> 00:10:53.778
She said he made her sign
a consent form before sex,

00:10:53.862 --> 00:10:55.864
like some kind of ritual.

00:10:56.573 --> 00:10:57.448
How thorough.

00:10:58.032 --> 00:10:58.992
How about alcohol?

00:10:59.075 --> 00:11:01.077
If she was intoxicated at the time
she gave consent,

00:11:01.161 --> 00:11:03.663
we could argue she lacked capacity,
so the consent wouldn't hold.

00:11:03.746 --> 00:11:05.415
I asked her that too,

00:11:06.207 --> 00:11:08.376
but she can't drink at all,
so that never happened.

00:11:08.459 --> 00:11:09.711
This is difficult.

00:11:10.753 --> 00:11:12.797
To establish assault,

00:11:13.464 --> 00:11:16.342
we'd have to argue
that the consent was not valid.

00:11:18.761 --> 00:11:19.846
Why is that?

00:11:20.680 --> 00:11:23.766
What does the validity of consent
have to do with assault?

00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:25.768
Jeez, you scared me.

00:11:26.728 --> 00:11:29.147
If I were to flick
your forehead right now,

00:11:29.230 --> 00:11:30.106
would that be assault?

00:11:30.190 --> 00:11:31.649
Of course.

00:11:31.733 --> 00:11:35.195
Then what if we both agreed
to a forehead flick if we lost a game?

00:11:35.278 --> 00:11:36.905
- That's not assault.
- Why not?

00:11:39.657 --> 00:11:40.533
I don't know.

00:11:40.617 --> 00:11:43.328
What about boxing?
They hit each other. Isn't that assault?

00:11:43.411 --> 00:11:45.079
That's not assault.

00:11:45.163 --> 00:11:46.372
Why not?

00:11:46.456 --> 00:11:48.416
Because it's a sport.

00:11:48.499 --> 00:11:51.502
In principle, the act itself
constitutes assault,

00:11:51.586 --> 00:11:53.922
but because the other party consented,

00:11:54.005 --> 00:11:55.840
it doesn't amount to a crime.

00:11:57.425 --> 00:12:00.303
Say you were a victim of school violence

00:12:00.386 --> 00:12:03.139
and only agreed to the forehead flick game

00:12:03.223 --> 00:12:06.476
out of fear of retaliation.
Would that consent still be valid?

00:12:07.060 --> 00:12:09.229
That's not genuine consent,
so it's assault.

00:12:09.312 --> 00:12:10.313
Exactly.

00:12:10.396 --> 00:12:12.565
For consent to negate
the unlawfulness of the act,

00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:15.944
it must be given by the victim
while in a state capable of making

00:12:16.027 --> 00:12:16.945
a voluntary decision.

00:12:17.028 --> 00:12:18.947
A straightforward example would be

00:12:19.030 --> 00:12:21.699
someone signing a contract
while under the influence of drugs,

00:12:21.783 --> 00:12:25.328
under hypnosis,
or with a knife pointed at them.

00:12:25.411 --> 00:12:28.790
That can't be considered
genuine consent, so--

00:12:28.873 --> 00:12:31.501
It can't be regarded
as a valid expression of consent.

00:12:32.126 --> 00:12:34.003
So that's why it constitutes assault.

00:12:34.087 --> 00:12:34.963
Exactly.

00:12:36.339 --> 00:12:38.758
There was written consent,

00:12:38.841 --> 00:12:41.219
but there may be room
to argue one key point…

00:12:41.302 --> 00:12:44.973
- Which is?
- Ms. Seol was in love.

00:12:46.266 --> 00:12:48.893
Therefore, she was in a state
of diminished capacity.

00:12:49.560 --> 00:12:50.436
What?

00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:53.648
Can't we say love is
a form of diminished capacity too?

00:12:56.901 --> 00:12:58.403
You never disappoint.

00:12:58.486 --> 00:13:00.405
How creative. Good job, Hyo-min.

00:13:00.488 --> 00:13:03.491
That's the funniest thing
I've heard recently.

00:13:03.574 --> 00:13:05.243
